-- Cyprus Sees 500 Million Euros From Casino Permits, Politis Says
-- B y   S t e l i o s   O r p h a n i d e s
-- 2012-02-15T14:30:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-15/cyprus-sees-500-million-euros-from-casino-permits-politis-says.html
Cyprus may get as much as 500
million euros ($655 million) from the sale of as many as five
casino licenses,  Politis  reported today, citing a  finance
ministry  report.  Annual tax revenue from the operation of the casinos may
reach as much as 50 million euros, the Nicosia-based newspaper
said.  -- Editors: James Kraus, Tim Farrand  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stelios Orphanides in Nicosia at  
